modules.description: This module defines infix operators for combining parser values, enabling concise composition of alternatives, sequences, prefixes, and suffixes. It operates on values of type `'a Tyre.t`, representing parsers that can consume input and produce values. Concrete use cases include building complex URL or string parsers by combining simpler parsers using familiar operator syntax.

This module provides parser combinators and typed regex utilities for structured text processing, enabling operations like sequencing, alternation, and value conversion over string inputs. It works with parsers that produce typed values (`'a t`), regex patterns with transformations, and route definitions that map patterns to typed outputs. Common use cases include bidirectional URL routing, parsing formatted data (e.g., logs, config files), and extracting structured values (integers, floats, lists) with error-resilient regex matching.
